    <thetext>The PDF version of the spec is missing two very handy features: The PDF table of contents and clickable cross-references. The PDF table of contents can be shown, for example, in the side bar of the Preview application on Mac. Clickable cross-references let you jump, e.g., from section 10.2.3 to 9.1 by clicking the cross-reference &quot;9.1&quot;. Both features are present in the PDF version of the first edition.

I suspect both features are missing because the Mac version of Word is crippled and doesn&apos;t support them. PDF versions of ECMAScript standards should therefore be generated on Windows.</thetext>
